    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You channel all of your might into your blade and take a mighty swing, casting all enemies aside. This jutsu can be used as an action or full turn action for a specific cost.</p><p><strong>Action (6 Chakra):</strong> Make a melee Taijutsu attack and compare the result against all hostile creatures around you within your weapon's range. Your weapon is treated as having the Reach(1) property for this jutsu, it has no Reach. If your attack roll matches or exceeds a target's AC, the creature takes your weapon's damage + 4d8 and must succeed a Strength save or be knocked back 15 feet and fall prone.</p><p><strong>Full Turn Action (9 Chakra):</strong> You begin spinning widely, moving up to your movement speed in any direction (Max. 60ft). Each creature that would be caught within your weapon's range, once per turn, must make a Dexterity saving throw, taking your weapon's damage + 5d4 on a failed save, or half as much on a success.</p><p>After casting this jutsu as a full turn action, at the start of your subsequent turns you can immediately cast this jutsu again as a full turn action at half cost. If you perform this jutsu for 2 or more turns consecutively, once you stop using this jutsu, you are Dazed until the start of your next turn as you feel motion sick.</p><p><strong>At Higher Ranks:</strong> For each rank you cast this jutsu above C-Rank, increase the cost of this jutsu by 3 and the damage by 2d8 or 2d4 respectively.</p>",
